==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foehn
<hw>Foehn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. dial. (Swiss),
fr. L. <ets>Favonius</ets> west wind. Cf. <er>Favonian</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A warm dry wind that often blows
in the northern valleys of the Alps, due to the indraught of a storm
center passing over Central Europe. The wind, heated by compression in
its descent from the mountains, reaches the base, particularly in
winter, dry and warm.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any similar wind, as the
chinook, in other parts of the world.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foehood</ent>⟦br⟧
